<TITLE> Blanc role to be confirmed after World Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, May 22 (bdnews24.com/AFP) -- The French Football Federation (FFF) will not confirm Laurent Blanc's instalment as the new France coach until after the World Cup in South Africa, a source told AFP on Friday. The FFF on Thursday announced that Blanc had agreed to replace Raymond Domenech after the June 11-July 11 tournament, but the FFF hopes to conclude the accompanying negotiations before the event. "The idea is to do it as quickly as possible and to announce it after the World Cup," said a member of the FFF's federal council who wished to remain anonymous and added that Blanc will be on holiday from May 28. "It should be done after the World Cup because both parties are in agreement." Blanc, who led Bordeaux to a league and League Cup double in 2009, is likely to be aided in his duties as France coach by long-time assistant Jean-Louis Gasset. According to French sport daily L'Equipe, Bordeaux will receive 1.5 million euros in compensa
